88	
89	---
90	
91	## 6. Layout Rules
92	
93	### Scaffold Structure
94	
95	- `Scaffold` with `ListView` body
96	- `AppBar`: Title "Health Log", back button, trailing filter icon button
97	- `BottomNavigationBar`: Hidden (per UX.md 3.6)
98	- `FAB`: `+` icon to add new entry, positioned bottom-right with safe area respect
99	
100	### AppBar Behavior
101	
102	- Background: `lavenderTint` (#F5F3FF)
103	- Title: "Health Log" (SemiBold 20sp, `deepGraphite`)
104	- Leading: Back button with 48dp touch target
105	- Trailing: Filter icon button (48dp touch target) to open filter options
106	
107	### Body Layout
108	
109	- `ListView` with `padding: EdgeInsets.symmetric(horizontal: 16dp, vertical: 24dp)`
110	- Summary stats banner at top (always visible)
111	- Timeline section below with chronological entries
112	- Bottom padding: 100dp to clear FAB and safe area
113	
114	### FAB Specifications
115	
116	- Size: 56dp diameter
117	- Background: `lavenderBloom` (#7C3AED)
118	- Icon: White, 24dp `Icons.add`
119	- Press feedback: 200ms scale to 90%
120	- Position: Bottom-right, 16dp from edges, respects safe area bottom
121	- FAB appearance: 200ms fade-in with subtle scale from 95% to 100%
122	
123	---
124	
125	## 7. Sections
126	
127	### Section 1: Summary Stats Banner
128	
129	**Description:** Top banner displaying aggregate health metrics — total symptoms logged this week and next upcoming reminder.
130	
131	**Widget Type:** `SliverToBoxAdapter` containing a horizontal card row
132	
133	**Layout:** Full-width card with 16dp internal padding, horizontal arrangement of stat items.
134	
135	**Components:**
136	- Card background: `morningMist` (#FAFAFA), 16dp corner radius, soft shadow
137	- Two stat items side-by-side:
138	  - Left: Symptom count badge with `lavenderBloom` icon + "X symptoms this week" text
139	  - Right: Next reminder with calendar icon + "Next: [reminder title] on [date]"
140	- If no entries exist: Show "No health entries yet" message
141	
142	**Data Requirements:**
143	- `SymptomEntryProvider.entries` filtered for current week
144	- `ReminderProvider.reminders` filtered for `isEnabled=true`, ordered by date, first item
145	
146	**Interactive Elements:**
147	- Tap symptom count → scrolls to first symptom entry in timeline
148	- Tap reminder → scrolls to that reminder entry in timeline
149	
150	---
151	
152	### Section 2: Timeline
153	
154	**Description:** Mixed chronological list of all health entries (symptoms, doctor visits, reminders) sorted by date descending.
155	
156	**Widget Type:** `SliverList` with `SliverChildBuilderDelegate`
157	
158	**Layout:** Vertical list with 12dp gap between items, grouped by date.
159	
160	**Components:**
161	
162	Each timeline entry card:
163	- Entry type indicator: Left border accent (4dp wide)
164	  - SymptomEntry: `lavenderBloom` (#7C3AED)
165	  - DoctorVisit: `blushRose` (#F9A8D4)
166	  - Reminder: `softMint` (#6EE7B7)
167	- Entry date header: "Today", "Yesterday", or formatted date ("May 15, 2024")
168	- Entry content varies by type:
169	
170	**SymptomEntry Card:**
171	- Symptom type name (`titleMedium`)
172	- Severity indicator: 1-3 dots or chips (mild/moderate/severe)
173	- Notes preview (`bodyMedium`, truncated to 1 line)
174	- Timestamp: "2:30 PM"
175	
176	**DoctorVisit Card:**
177	- Doctor name (`titleMedium`)
178	- Visit purpose/notes (`bodyMedium`, truncated)
179	- Next visit date if set (caption with `softMint` accent)
180	- Timestamp
181	
182	**Reminder Card:**
183	- Reminder title (`titleMedium`)
184	- Category badge chip
185	- Due date/time
186	- Enabled/disabled indicator
187	
188	**Date Grouping:**
189	- Entries grouped by date with sticky date headers
190	- Date headers: `caption` style, `stoneGrey`, left-aligned
191	
192	**Empty State:**
193	- Centered illustration placeholder
194	- "No health entries logged" message
195	- "Tap + to add your first entry" subtitle
196	
197	**Data Requirements:**
198	- Combine entries from: `SymptomEntryProvider`, `DoctorVisitProvider`, `ReminderProvider`
199	- Sort all by date descending
200	- Fields per entity:
201	  - SymptomEntry: `date`, `symptomType`, `severity` (1-3), `notes`
202	  - DoctorVisit: `date`, `doctorName`, `notes`, `nextVisitDate`
203	  - Reminder: `title`, `date`, `category`, `isEnabled`
204	
205	**Interactive Elements:**
206	- Tap entry → detail bottom sheet
207	- Long-press entry → edit/delete bottom sheet
208	- Pull-to-refresh → reloads all providers
209	
210	---
211	
212	### Section 3 (Overlay): Add Entry Bottom Sheet
213	
214	**Description:** Entry type selector and form for creating new health entries.
215	
216	**Trigger:** Tap FAB `+`
217	
218	**Widget Type:** `showModalBottomSheet` with `SingleChildScrollView`
219	
220	**Layout:** Bottom sheet with 28dp top corner radius, handle bar, max 90% screen height.
221	
222	**Components:**
223	- Handle bar: 40dp wide, 4dp tall, centered, `stoneGrey` color
224	- Title: "Add Entry" (`titleLarge`)
225	- Entry type selector: 3 horizontal chips/cards
226	  - "Symptom" — symptom icon
227	  - "Doctor Visit" — medical icon
228	  - "Reminder" — bell icon
229	- Form fields depend on selected type
230	- Action buttons: "Cancel" (text), "Save" (primary pill button)
231	- Form validation per entry type
232	
233	**Data Operations:**
234	- On save: Call appropriate provider's `addEntry()` method
235	
236	---
237	
238	### Section 4 (Overlay): Filter Options Bottom Sheet
239	
240	**Description:** Filter timeline by entry type and date range.
241	
242	**Trigger:** Tap filter icon in AppBar
243	
244	**Widget Type:** `showModalBottomSheet` with `Column`
245	
246	**Layout:** Bottom sheet with 28dp top corner radius, handle bar.
247	
248	**Components:**
249	- Handle bar
250	- Title: "Filter Entries" (`titleLarge`)
251	- Entry type filter: Checkbox list
252	  - [ ] Symptoms
253	  - [ ] Doctor Visits
254	  - [ ] Reminders
255	- Date range: "This week", "This month", "All time" (chip selector)
256	- "Apply" primary button
257	- "Clear filters" text button
258	
259	---
260	
261	### Section 5 (Overlay): Entry Detail/Edit Bottom Sheet
262	
263	**Description:** View, edit, or delete existing entries.
264	
265	**Trigger:** Tap timeline entry
266	
267	**Components:**
268	- Header: Entry type icon + date
269	- Symptom type display/edit
270	- Severity selector: 1-3 rating with labels (Mild, Moderate, Severe)
271	- Date picker
272	- Notes field (multi-line)
273	- Delete button (`softCoral` text button)
274	- Save button
275	
276	---
277	
278	## 8. Data
279	
280	### Entity: SymptomEntry
281	
282	| Field | Type | Required | Description |
283	|---|---|---|---|
284	| `id` | `String` (UUID) | Yes | Unique identifier |
285	| `date` | `DateTime` | Yes | Entry timestamp |
286	| `symptomType` | `String` | Yes | Type of symptom (e.g., "Headache", "Nausea") |
287	| `severity` | `int` (1-3) | Yes | 1=mild, 2=moderate, 3=severe |
288	| `notes` | `String` | No | Additional notes |
289	
290	### Entity: DoctorVisit
291	
292	| Field | Type | Required | Description |
293	|---|---|---|---|
294	| `id` | `String` (UUID) | Yes | Unique identifier |
295	| `date` | `DateTime` | Yes | Visit date |
296	| `doctorName` | `String` | Yes | Doctor or clinic name |
297	| `notes` | `String` | No | Visit notes |
298	| `nextVisitDate` | `DateTime` | No | Scheduled follow-up |
299	
300	### Entity: Reminder
301	
302	| Field | Type | Required | Description |
303	|---|---|---|---|
304	| `id` | `String` (UUID) | Yes | Unique identifier |
305	| `title` | `String` | Yes | Reminder title |
306	| `date` | `DateTime` | Yes | Reminder date/time |
307	| `category` | `String` | No | Category (e.g., "Medication", "Appointment") |
308	| `isEnabled` | `bool` | Yes | Whether reminder is active |
309	
310	### Provider: SymptomEntryProvider
311	
312	**State:**
313	- `entries: List<SymptomEntry>` — all logged symptoms
314	
315	**Methods:**
316	- `addEntry(entry)` — adds new symptom entry
317	- `updateEntry(id, entry)` — modifies existing entry
318	- `deleteEntry(id)` — removes entry
319	- `getThisWeekEntries()` — filters entries to current week
320	
321	### Provider: DoctorVisitProvider
322	
323	**State:**
324	- `visits: List<DoctorVisit>` — all logged visits
325	
326	**Methods:**
327	- `addVisit(visit)` — adds new visit
328	- `updateVisit(id, visit)` — modifies existing visit
329	- `deleteVisit(id)` — removes visit
330	
331	### Provider: ReminderProvider
332	
333	**State:**
334	- `reminders: List<Reminder>` — all reminders
335	
336	**Methods:**
337	- `addReminder(reminder)` — adds new reminder
338	- `updateReminder(id, reminder)` — modifies existing reminder
339	- `deleteReminder(id)` — removes reminder
340	- `getUpcomingEnabled()` — returns enabled reminders sorted by date
341	
342	---
343	
344	## 9. Motion
345	
346	### Entry Animations
347	
348	- Screen push: 300ms slide + fade (standard page transition)
349	- Summary stats card: 200ms fade-in on load
350	- Timeline items: Staggered reveal, 50ms delay between items, 200ms per item fade+slide
351	
352	### Bottom Sheet Animations
353	
354	- FAB to sheet: 250ms smooth deceleration slide-up
355	- Sheet dismiss: 200ms slide-down with fade
356	
357	### Interactive Feedback
358	
359	- Entry card tap: 200ms scale to 98% with shadow lift
360	- FAB press: 200ms scale to 90%, shadow intensifies
361	- Filter chip selection: 150ms opacity/color transition
362	- Save button: 200ms scale to 95%
363	
364	### Pull-to-refresh
365	
366	- 150ms duration, quick snap
367	- Refresh indicator appears and dismisses quickly
368	
369	---
370	
371	## 10. Accessibility
372	
373	### Semantic Labels
374	
375	| Element | Semantic Label |
376	|---|---|
377	| AppBar | `'Health Log, back button to return to Library, filter button'` |
378	| Filter button | `'Filter entries, double tap to open filter options'` |
379	| Summary stats | `'Health summary, X symptoms this week, next reminder on [date]'` |
380	| FAB | `'Add new health entry, double tap to open form'` |
381	| Symptom entry | `'$symptomType, $severity severity, $notes, $time'` |
382	| Doctor visit | `'Doctor visit with $doctorName, $notes, $time'` |
383	| Reminder | `'$title reminder, $category, $date, ${isEnabled ? 'enabled' : 'disabled'}'` |
384	| Date header | `'$date, $count entries'` |
385	
386	### Focus Order
387	
388	1. AppBar (back button → filter button)
389	2. Summary stats card
390	3. Timeline entries (in date order, most recent first)
391	4. FAB
392	
393	### Contrast Notes
394	
395	- `lavenderBloom` on `lavenderTint`: ~4.5:1 (passes AA)
396	- `deepGraphite` on `morningMist`: ~12:1 (passes AAA)
397	- `stoneGrey` on white: ~4.7:1 (passes AA for body text)
398	- Entry type accent colors used as borders, not backgrounds, for visibility
399	
400	### Screen Reader Support
401	
402	- Announce entry added: "Health entry saved"
403	- Announce deletion: "Entry deleted"
404	- Announce filter applied: "Showing $filteredTypes entries"
405	- Use `Semantics` to label entry severity (e.g., "Severity: 2 out of 3, moderate")
406	
407	### Touch Target Compliance
408	
409	- All interactive elements: 48dp minimum
410	- FAB: 56dp (exceeds minimum)
411	- Timeline entries: Full card tap, 56dp+ height
412	- All buttons: 48dp minimum height
413	- Filter chips: 48dp minimum height
414	
415	---
416	
417	## 11. Anti-Patterns
418	
419	**Do Not:**
420	- Use `GridView` for timeline (simple `ListView` with date grouping is appropriate)
421	- Add `BottomNavigationBar` (hidden per UX spec)
422	- Show FAB on initial load without animation (fade-in over 200ms)
423	- Mix entry types inconsistently — always show type indicator
424	- Use hard-coded symptom types (use provider data)
425	- Place FAB in bottom center (bottom-right per design system)
426	- Use pure black text on backgrounds
427	- Use Inter, Roboto, or any font other than Nunito
428	- Add shadows to AppBar (transparent/floating style)
429	- Use `Navigator.push` instead of `context.push` with GoRouter
430	- Skip safe area handling for FAB position
431	- Display empty state without illustration/guidance text
432	- Use gradients on cards — flat `morningMist` only
433	- Skip entry type indicator (accessibility issue)
434	
435	---
